        "index": 17,
        "tags": [
            "team_prediction"
        ],
        "content": [
            "## [New England Patriots](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/</nfl/team/_/name/ne/new-england-patriots>)",
            "**Don\\'t be surprised if ... rookie[TreVeyon Henderson](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/<https:/www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4432710/treveyon-henderson>) is the team\\'s No. 1 running back all season.**",
            "**What I\\'m hearing:** If you\\'ve been prepping for fantasy drafts, you\\'re already all over this. Henderson has been the most explosive element of the Patriots\\' offense throughout camp, and the coaching staff is smart enough to know New England needs some explosiveness. The concerns about Henderson are whether he can hold up to a full-time starting RB\\'s workload, considering he split carries with [Quinshon Judkins](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/<https:/www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4685702/quinshon-judkins>) last year at Ohio State. [Rhamondre Stevenson](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/<https:/www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4569173/rhamondre-stevenson>) is still there if the Patriots want to keep the rookie\\'s workload lighter early in the season. But there\\'s some sentiment in Foxborough that Henderson is going to be the type of player they don\\'t want to take off the field."
        ],
        "error": false
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "tags": [
            "team_prediction"
        ],
        "content": [
            "## [New York Jets](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/</nfl/team/_/name/nyj/new-york-jets>)",
            "**Don\\'t be surprised if ... the Jets lead the league in rushing.**",
            "**What I\\'m hearing:** They\\'re extremely high on second-year running back [Braelon Allen](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/<https:/www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4685247/braelon-allen>), the 2024 fourth-round draft pick who\\'s still only 21 years old. They also know what they have in [Breece Hall](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/<https:/www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4427366/breece-hall>), who can be a primary ball carrier, a receiving back or some combination of the two. And in [Justin Fields](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/<https:/www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4362887/justin-fields>), the Jets have one of the most electrifying runners at the quarterback position the league has ever seen. This team\\'s offensive DNA is going to lie in its run game. And if Fields can show a consistent ability to get the ball downfield to [Garrett Wilson](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/<https:/www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4569618/garrett-wilson>) in the passing game, it will only open things up more for the Jets to run, run, run."
        ],
        "error": false
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "tags": [
            "team_prediction"
        ],
        "content": [
            "## AFC NORTH",
            "## [Baltimore Ravens](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/</nfl/team/_/name/bal/baltimore-ravens>)",
            "**Don\\'t be surprised if ... wide receiver[Zay Flowers](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/<https:/www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4429615/zay-flowers>) takes a third-year leap.**",
            "**What I\\'m hearing:** The Ravens\\' offensive identity is still going to be in their outstanding run game, but Flowers is their No. 1 wide receiver, and his absence from last season\\'s divisional round playoff game in Buffalo (knee) played a part in [their loss](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/</nfl/game/_/gameId/401671886/ravens-bills>). He\\'s healthy now and has had a nice camp. But the main reason I\\'m looking out for Flowers this season is the fact that [DeAndre Hopkins](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/<https:/www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/15795/deandre-hopkins>) has been on the team since the spring. Last year at the Super Bowl, Chiefs coaches were raving to me about the impact Hopkins had after Kansas City acquired him -- not as a pass catcher but as a teacher, particularly for rookie wideout [Xavier Worthy](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/<https:/www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/4683062/xavier-worthy>). They talked about how Hopkins would grab the tablet after a drive, walk over to Worthy and teach him some of the finer details about route-running techniques. They felt Worthy\\'s improved performance throughout the season was due in part to Hopkins\\' help, and Ravens coach John Harbaugh told me when I visited their camp that he has seen similar things from Hopkins since he has been in Baltimore. Perhaps Hopkins has the same kind of impact on Flowers that he had on Worthy."
        ],
        "error": false
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "tags": [
            "team_prediction"
        ],
        "content": [
            "## [Cincinnati Bengals](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/</nfl/team/_/name/cin/cincinnati-bengals>)",
            "**Don\\'t be surprised if ... the Bengals return to the AFC Championship Game.**",
            "**What I\\'m hearing:** The outside concern about the way the defense has looked in preseason games is not shared by those inside the building. The Bengals are installing a new scheme under new defensive coordinator Al Golden, and the coaching staff made a conscious decision to put as little of that scheme on tape as possible in the televised preseason games. People who have been at practice say the first-team defense has performed fairly well against [Joe Burrow](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/<https:/www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/3915511/joe-burrow>) and one of the best offenses in the NFL -- even with defensive end [Trey Hendrickson](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/<https:/www.espn.com/nfl/player/_/id/3052743/trey-hendrickson>) not participating before agreeing to his [new deal](https://www.espn.com/nfl/story/_/id/46079215/</nfl/story/_/id/46073993/sources-bengals-give-trey-hendrickson-big-pay-bump-hold-in>). Cincinnati\\'s defense has only one direction to go after last season\\'s collapse. Opponents scored 25.5 points per game on the Bengals, tied for seventh most in the league. If that unit can get back to even the middle of the pack, this is a dangerous team with a potent offense and players who know how to win playoff games. As poorly as the past two seasons have gone in Cincinnati, the Bengals still managed to finish 9-8 in both of them. If that\\'s rock bottom, you have a contending roster."
        ],
        "error": false
    }
]

